text: hi Eugene what brings you in today
Hey there. I've been feeling worn out all the time, and my legs swell up pretty bad. Just trying to figure out what's going on.
are you having any pain today
I've got this deep ache in my bones, like I've been hauling pipe all day. It's been bothering me a bit.
when did it start
It started getting worse after I stopped working, but I've noticed it for a while now.
why did you stop working
I stopped working because I was too tired and weak to keep up with my plumbing jobs. Just couldn't do it anymore.
is the pain all over is there specific location
The ache is mostly in my bones, but my arms and legs feel weak too. It's like my whole body’s giving out.
is there anything that makes your symptoms better or worse
Resting seems to help a little, but not much. Moving around too much or trying to lift things makes it worse.
is your pain worse at a specific time of day
It's mostly the same throughout the day, but it feels worse when I'm trying to sleep at night.
what symptoms do you have at night
At night, my legs won't stop moving, and it keeps me up. I also wake up with this white powder on my skin — looks like frost.
does your skin feel dry
Yeah, my skin does feel dry sometimes, especially when I see that white powdery stuff on it.
can you rate the pain on a scale of 1 to 10 one being not so bad and 10 being the worst pain
I'd say it's around a 6. It's not unbearable, but it's definitely there and annoying.
did you change anything about your routine or notice any patterns associated with the symptoms
I haven't changed much about my routine, but I've noticed that the symptoms seem worse when I'm more active or try to do too much. Resting helps a bit, but not enough to make a big difference.
have you ever had these issues before
Not like this. I've had high blood pressure for a while, but these new symptoms — the fatigue, swelling, and everything else — are pretty recent.
did you have any other symptoms that started besides the fatigue swelling
Yeah, I feel nauseated most days, and everything tastes like metal. There's also this ammonia smell that won't go away, and my girlfriend says my breath smells fishy.
have you had any episodes of vomiting
Yeah, I've vomited a few times lately. It's been happening more often now.
have you ever been diagnosed with anything before
I've had high blood pressure since my thirties and had a mild stroke a while back. That's about it.
do you take any medications regularly
I have a whole bunch of medicines I'm on that I can't pronounce. My girlfriend makes me keep a list in my wallet.
can we see the list
Sure, the list includes furosemide, nifedipine, potassium chloride, clonidine patch, clopidogrel, atenolol, iron, and aspirin.
do you know what you take those medications for
Not exactly. I know they're mostly for my blood pressure and keeping things in check, but my doctor handles the details.
do you smoke tobacco
No, I don't smoke.
any alcohol use
I sometimes go out for a few beers on Fridays, but not often.
how's your diet and exercise

I try to avoid too much salt, though it's hard when everything tastes like metal. My girlfriend and I eat out on weekends. As for exercise, I haven't been able to do much lately because of the fatigue and weakness.
allergies
None that I know of.
any past or recent trauma or surgeries
No, I haven't had any trauma or surgeries recently or in the past.
have you had any skin changes
Yeah, I've noticed bruises showing up for no reason, and my skin itches when my legs are swollen. There's also that white powdery stuff I wake up with.
where are the bruises located
The bruises seem to show up mostly on my arms and legs.
are your family members healthy
My dad had high blood pressure and diabetes, and he died young at 45. My mom had breast cancer and passed away at 60.
do you ever get your blood sugar or blood pressure checked
Yeah, I get my blood pressure checked regularly since it's been high for a while. I haven't had my blood sugar checked recently, though.
any urinary changes that you've noticed blood in your urine change in color or smell with your urine
I pee less than I used to, and sometimes it's darker. I figured I just wasn't drinking enough. No blood that I've noticed.
have you had any recent illness
I haven't had any recent illnesses, but I've been feeling worn out and sick most days with these new symptoms.
abdominal pain nausea vomiting or diarrhea
I feel nauseated most days and have vomited a few times lately. No abdominal pain or diarrhea, though.

have you had any headache, lightheadedness, fever, weight change, chest pain, shortness of breath, palpitations, dental problems, abdominal pain, numbness, tingling, vision changes, changes in smell, heat or cold intolerance

I get dizzy if I stand up too fast, and I've lost weight without trying. I feel short of breath when I walk too far or climb stairs. My fingers and toes tingle or go numb sometimes. My girlfriend says my eyes look like they're bulging, and I can't shake this ammonia smell that's always there. No fever, chest pain, or dental problems.
have you ever fractured a bone
No, I've never fractured a bone.
any sweating
Yeah, I sweat out of nowhere sometimes, especially at night.
have you had any blood loss and do you drink enough water
I haven't noticed any blood loss. I try to drink enough water, but sometimes my urine's dark, so maybe I need to drink more.
I've got a cough
I haven't had a cough myself, but if you're dealing with one, it might be good to keep an eye on it or check in with a doctor. Anything else you want to know?
